<dl id="n58069a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n58" href="#n58069a">N58 (VI.B.30)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n58all.htm#n58069a"> 69(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> 400 millions / of miles <small>Green</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n58069a"> <li>FW unlocated</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Calculations have shown that these perspective appearances are caused by the translation of the sun, the earth, and all the planets towards a region of the sky marked by the constellation Hercules. We travel towards that region with a velocity that is difficult to determine exactly, but which appears to be from <mark>400 to 500 millions of miles</mark> per annum. <small> Camille Flammarion, <a name="CFPA" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CFPA"><cite title="source">Popular Astronomy</cite></a> (1907) 50</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
